90 std::string
91 constructErrorMessage(const char *fmt, ...)
92 {
93  char msg[BUFSIZ];
94  va_list args;
95  va_start(args, fmt);
96  int nbytes = vsnprintf(msg, BUFSIZ, fmt, args);
97  va_end(args);
98  if(BUFSIZ <= nbytes)
99  {
100  return std::string();
101  }
102  return std::string(msg);
103 }

107 class AssignedParamCreator
108  :public SingleParameter::Visitor,
109  public ParameterArrayElement::Visitor,
110  public ParameterArray::Visitor {
111  public:
112  void
113  visit(SingleParameter &single) throw(Error)
114  try
115  {
116  SingleParameterSharedPtr singleP;
117  mFactory->create(singleP);
118  singleP->setName(single.getName());
119  singleP->setValue(mValues[0]);
120  mMap->set(mContext, single.getName(), singleP);
121  }
122  catch(Error &e)
123  {
124  e.setCurrentLocation(
125  __FUNCTION__, __FILE__, __LINE__ );
126  throw;
127  }
128 
129  void
130  visit(ParameterArrayElement &element) throw(Error)
131  try
132  {
133  ParameterSharedPtr array
134  = element.getParentCollection();
135  if(array == mMap->get(mContext, array->getName()))
136  {
137  AssignedParamCreator creator(
138  mInstance, mContext, mMap, mFactory, mValues );
139  array->accept(creator);
140  }
141  std::vector<size_t> indices = element.getIndices();
142  ParameterSharedPtr arrayP
143  = mMap->get(mContext, array->getName());
144  ParameterSharedPtr bit = arrayP->get(indices);
145  bit->setValue(mValues[0]);
146  }
147  catch(Error &e)
148  {
149  e.setCurrentLocation(
150  __FUNCTION__, __FILE__, __LINE__ );
151  throw;
152  }
153 
154  void
155  visit(ParameterArray &array) throw(Error)
156  try
157  {
158  std::vector<size_t> limits;
159  array.getLimits(limits);
160  ParameterArraySharedPtr arrayP;
161  mFactory->create(arrayP);
162  arrayP->setName(array.getName());
163  std::vector<size_t> dimensions;
164  array.getLimits(dimensions);
165  arrayP->constructChildren(mFactory, limits);
166  std::vector< ParameterSharedPtr > children;
167  arrayP->getChildren(children);
168  std::vector< ParameterSharedPtr >::iterator
169  it = children.begin();
170  std::vector< ParameterSharedPtr >::iterator
171  end = children.end();
172  size_t i = 0;
173  for(; it != end; ++it, i++ )
174  {
175  (*it)->setValue(mValues[i]);
176  }
177  mMap->set(mContext, array.getName(), arrayP);
178  }
179  catch(Error &e)
180  {
181  e.setCurrentLocation(
182  __FUNCTION__, __FILE__, __LINE__ );
183  throw;
184  }

210 template <typename _Connectable>
211 void
212 connectibleFinder( std::vector< std::string > &nestedNames,
213  boost::shared_ptr<_Connectable> &conn ) throw(Error)
214 {
215  std::vector< std::string >::reverse_iterator name
216  = nestedNames.rbegin();
217  std::vector< std::string >::reverse_iterator end
218  = nestedNames.rend();
219  ++name;
220  if(!conn)
221  {
222  std::string message = constructErrorMessage(
223  "Nested connectible name %s not found",
224  (*name).c_str() );
225  log("%s\n", message.c_str());
226  Error e( eMessageIdErrorNullPointer,
227  __FUNCTION__, __FILE__, __LINE__ );
228  throw e;
229  }
230  for(;name != end; ++name)
231  {
232  if( eCompositionTypeBundle
233  != conn->getCompositionType() )
234  {
235  log("Item is not a bundle .. invalid nesting\n");
236  Error e( eMessageIdErrorUnsupoortedOperation,
237  __FUNCTION__, __FILE__, __LINE__ );
238  e.saveContextData("Name", *name );
239  e.saveContextData("Operation",
240  std::string("Find child") );
241  throw e;
242  }
243  std::vector< boost::shared_ptr<_Connectable> > children;
244  conn->getChildren(children);
245  bool found = false;
246  for( typename
247  std::vector< boost::shared_ptr<_Connectable> >::iterator
248  it = children.begin(); it != children.end(); ++it )
249  {
250  if((*it)->getName() == *name)
251  {
252  conn = (*it);
253  found = true;
254  break;
255  }
256  }
257  if(!found)
258  {
259  std::string message = constructErrorMessage(
260  "Nested connectible %s not found",
261  (*name).c_str() );
262  log("%s\n", message.c_str());
263  Error e( eMessageIdErrorItemNotFound,
264  __FUNCTION__, __FILE__, __LINE__ );
265  e.saveContextData("Name", (*name));
266  throw e;
267  }
268  }
269 }

271 template <typename _Connectable>
272 void
273 portJoiner( NameData *inPortNameData,
274  const boost::shared_ptr<_Connectable> &inConn,
275  const NetSharedPtr &inNet ) throw(Error)
276 {
277  try
278  {
279  if(inPortNameData->mIndices.empty())
280  {
281  //TBD::CHECK WIDTH
282  inConn->connect(inNet);
283  }
284  else
285  {
286  boost::shared_ptr<_Connectable> bit
287  = inConn->get(inPortNameData->mIndices);
288  bit->connect(inNet);
289  }
290  log( "Net %s connected with connectible %s\n",
291  inNet->getName().c_str(), inConn->getName().c_str() );
292  }
293  catch(Error &e)
294  {
295  e.setCurrentLocation(__FUNCTION__, __FILE__, __LINE__);
296  throw;
297  }
298 }

300 void
301 connectElementToNet( PortRefData *inPortData,
302  const EdifContextSharedPtr &inContext,
303  Parser::location_type& inLocation,
304  std::string &outErrorMessage ) throw(Error)
305 {
306  PortRefData *portData = inPortData;
307  std::vector< std::string > nestedNames;
308  PortRefData *currPortRef = inPortData;
309  PortRefData *nextPortRef = portData->mParentPort;
310  nestedNames.push_back(currPortRef->mPortName->mName);
311  while(nextPortRef)
312  {
313  currPortRef = nextPortRef;
314  nestedNames.push_back(nextPortRef->mPortName->mName);
315  nextPortRef = currPortRef->mParentPort;
316  }
317  bool isPort = (NULL == currPortRef->mInstanceName);
318  NameData *portNameData = currPortRef->mPortName;
319  std::string topName = *(nestedNames.rbegin());
320  EdifContextSharedPtr ctx = inContext;
321  ViewSharedPtr view = ctx->getCurrentView();
322  if(isPort)
323  {
324  PortSharedPtr port = view->findPort(topName);
325  if(!port)
326  {
327  std::string message = constructErrorMessage(
328  "No port %s found",
329  portNameData->mName.c_str());
330  log("%s\n", message.c_str());
331  Error e( eMessageIdParserError,
332  __FUNCTION__, __FILE__, __LINE__ );
333  e.saveContextData("Parser error message", message);
334  e.saveContextData("Filename", inLocation.begin.filename);
335  e.saveContextData("StartLine", inLocation.begin.line);
336  e.saveContextData("EndLine", inLocation.end.line);
337  outErrorMessage = message;
338  throw e;
339  }
340  try
341  {
342  NetSharedPtr net = ctx->getCurrentNet();
343  connectibleFinder(nestedNames, port);
344  portJoiner(portData->mPortName, port, net);
345  }
346  catch(Error &e)
347  {
348  std::string message = constructErrorMessage(
349  "Unable to connect port : %s", port->getName().c_str());
350  log("%s\n", message.c_str());
351  e.setCurrentLocation( __FUNCTION__,
352  __FILE__, __LINE__ );
353  e.saveContextData("Parser error message", message);
354  e.saveContextData("Filename", inLocation.begin.filename);
355  e.saveContextData("StartLine", inLocation.begin.line);
356  e.saveContextData("EndLine", inLocation.end.line);
357  outErrorMessage = message;
358  throw e;
359  }
360  }
361  else
362  {
363  NameData *instanceName
364  = currPortRef->mInstanceName;
365  InstanceSharedPtr instance
366  = view->findInstance(
367  instanceName->mName );
368  if(!instance)
369  {
370  std::string message = constructErrorMessage(
371  "Instance %s not known",
372  instanceName->mName.c_str() );
373  log("%s\n", message.c_str());
374  Error e( eMessageIdParserError,
375  __FUNCTION__, __FILE__, __LINE__ );
376  e.saveContextData("Parser error message", message);
377  e.saveContextData("Filename", inLocation.begin.filename);
378  e.saveContextData("StartLine", inLocation.begin.line);
379  e.saveContextData("EndLine", inLocation.end.line);
380  outErrorMessage = message;
381  throw e;
382  }
383  if(!instanceName->mIndices.empty())
384  {
385  InstanceSharedPtr bit
386  = instance->get(instanceName->mIndices);
387  instance = bit;
388  }
389  PortReferenceSharedPtr portRef
390  = instance->findPortReference(topName);
391  if(!portRef)
392  {
393  std::string message = constructErrorMessage(
394  "No port ref %s found",
395  portNameData->mName.c_str());
396  log("%s\n", message.c_str());
397  Error e( eMessageIdParserError,
398  __FUNCTION__, __FILE__, __LINE__ );
399  e.saveContextData("Parser error message", message);
400  e.saveContextData("Filename", inLocation.begin.filename);
401  e.saveContextData("StartLine", inLocation.begin.line);
402  e.saveContextData("EndLine", inLocation.end.line);
403  outErrorMessage = message;
404  throw e;
405  }
406  try
407  {
408  connectibleFinder(nestedNames, portRef);
409  portJoiner( portData->mPortName, portRef,
410  ctx->getCurrentNet() );
411  }
412  catch(Error &e)
413  {
414  std::string message = constructErrorMessage(
415  "Unable to connect port ref : %s", portRef->getName().c_str());
416  log("%s\n", message.c_str());
417  e.setCurrentLocation( __FUNCTION__,
418  __FILE__, __LINE__ );
419  e.saveContextData("Parser error message", message);
420  e.saveContextData("Filename", inLocation.begin.filename);
421  e.saveContextData("StartLine", inLocation.begin.line);
422  e.saveContextData("EndLine", inLocation.end.line);
423  outErrorMessage = message;
424  throw e;
425  }
426  }

505  /* Return YYSTR after stripping away unnecessary quotes and
506  backslashes, so that it's suitable for yyerror. The heuristic is
507  that double-quoting is unnecessary unless the string contains an
508  apostrophe, a comma, or backslash (other than backslash-backslash).
509  YYSTR is taken from yytname. */
510  std::string
511  Parser::yytnamerr_ (const char *yystr)
512  {
513  if (*yystr == '"')
514  {
515  std::string yyr = "";
516  char const *yyp = yystr;
517 
518  for (;;)
519  switch (*++yyp)
520  {
521  case '\'':
522  case ',':
523  goto do_not_strip_quotes;
524 
525  case '\\':
526  if (*++yyp != '\\')
527  goto do_not_strip_quotes;
528  /* Fall through. */
529  default:
530  yyr += *yyp;
531  break;
532 
533  case '"':
534  return yyr;
535  }
536  do_not_strip_quotes: ;
537  }
538 
539  return yystr;
540  }
541
